ZH: 我饿得狼吞虎咽地吃了一整碗面条。
EN: I wolfed down a whole bowl of noodles because I was starving.

ZH: 看他那副狼吞虎咽的样子，好像很久没吃东西了。
EN: Look at him, gobbling up his food like he hasn't eaten in ages.

ZH: 他下午打完球回来后，狼吞虎咽地喝了一瓶冷水。
EN: After playing basketball in the afternoon, he gulped down a bottle of cold water.

ZH: 大家在餐馆里都狼吞虎咽地吃完了晚饭。
EN: Everyone devoured their dinner in the restaurant.

ZH: 考试前，他以狼吞虎咽的速度把书上的知识点都背了一遍。
EN: Before the exam, he quickly crammed all the knowledge points in the book.

ZH: 看到这么多美食，我忍不住狼吞虎咽地想尝一尝。
EN: Seeing so much delicious food, I couldn't help but eagerly want to taste it.

ZH: 小狗饿极了，狼吞虎咽地吃完了一碗狗粮。
EN: The puppy, starving, gobbled up a bowl of dog food.

ZH: 他小时候总是狼吞虎咽，现在慢慢开始变得细嚼慢咽了。
EN: He used to wolf down his food as a child, but now he's starting to chew slowly.

ZH: 妈妈教育我要懂得细嚼慢咽，不要狼吞虎咽。
EN: My mom taught me to chew slowly and not to gulp down my food.

